AboutAbout

As the Director at the U.S. Department of Special Projects and Unified Response Services (US SPURS), I lead large-scale government projects and programs that require coordination, communication, and collaboration across multiple teams and organizational boundaries. With over 17 years of combined experience in the military and public service, I have developed a strong expertise in disaster and emergency planning, risk management and mitigation, development of cross-functional modular infrastructures and new organization development.

My mission is to maximize operational efficiency, reduce costs, and create an effective organization that supports the every American. I have a proven track record of motivating excellence non-traditional team cultivation strategies, development of leaders (not bosses or mangers) who hire and then inspire, and holding the line on not governmenting any process or service our Organization offers to the Public.

During my off work hours, I am blessed and passionate about working with at-risk youth and families alike , mentoring them, and providing them with the resources and opportunities they need to succeed. Remember, there is no such thing as a bad kid. When you look back far enough, theres always some adult that took great care to not allow that child to truly feel unconditionally loved and cared for.

I hold a PMI-RMP certification and a Bachelors in Business and Organizational Development, with certifications in within Public Safety and Government Programs.As the Director at the U.S. Department of Special Projects and Unified Response Services (US SPURS), I lead large-scale government projects and programs that require coordination, communication, and collaboration across multiple teams and organizational boundaries. With over 17 years of combined experience in the military and public service, I have developed a strong expertise in disaster and emergency planning, risk management and mitigation, development of cross-functional modular infrastructures and new organization development. Remember, there is no such thing as a bad kid. When you look back far enough, theres always some adult that took great care to not allow that child to truly feel unconditionally loved and cared for. I hold a PMI-RMP certification and a Bachelors in Business and Organizational Development, with certifications in within Public Safety and Government Programs.

      • EDviceU LLC provides innovative educational training through online and/or other remote means that help better prepare stakeholders for new opportunities within life or
        their careers. Teachers need help with technology training and ideas on how to implement it.

        Schools need to learn how to step back and allow educators to be innovative and explore new ways to deliver knowledge with a passion. If you want youth to be passionate about leaning, you must elevate and demonstrate trust in your employees ability to plan, create, deliver, evaluate and integrate a curriculum that meets the needs of the needs of students here and now. Not the student of 40 years ago.

        Many Parents also need resources for personal growth to change careers, promote or to simply sustain. We provide them with life, job and real world skills based training and job opportunities. Our research has shown many parents were never educated on those those highly important areas, through no fault of their own. You can not have real change in a community or the home unless you radically, quickly and aggressively work collectively to force a paradigm shift in overall family unit.

        Lastly, we work with the students to learn how to take an interactive and direct part in their educational and potential work journey. You can not expect a student to be engaged if you simply tell them they have to to learn because its what they have to do, without a why or a purpose. You need to listen and understand...yes, we said listen and understand what their concerns are, what they are curious about and then find out how to address their obstacles & foster curiosity.

        We have found if you stop teaching to test & start teaching to the hearts, minds & reality, you inspire a want to learn. This leads to shorter periods of instruction and an average 67% increase in long-term knowledge retention and faster recall. When you want to learn, you learn. When you hate learning & it feels like a choir, you avoid its lessons.       • Youth Services Consulting Group LLC (YSCG) provides a multitude of Wrap-Around services for Youth until the age of 24. Our main services is provided through our Behavioral Health Specialist (BHS) who work with schools to provide mental health treatment and/or counseling for individuals of all ages with emotional trauma, mental health concerns, intellectual underperformance, social anxiety, developmental disabilities and for those simply going through life and having a rough patch.

        We also provide services to those with co-occurring disorders, drug & alcohol addictions, and various other acute and chronic diagnoses. Our BHS are normally Licensed Marriage and Family Therapist, Associate Marriage and Family Therapist or Licensed Social Worker. We provide services to students regardless of MEDI-CAL Insurance since our contract with directly with individual school or school distract. Keep in mind, the more student's with service needs a school or district has, we would to hire additional staff to supplement as our max caseload per worker is set at 25 in order to provide the high level of services each student deserves.

        Our group of professionals includes staff trainers, marketing managers, social media managers, community outreach managers, compliance managers, counseling managers and many more.
